dleston, Cheshire, England":"Edleston, Cheshire, England","Egerton, Cheshire, England":"Egerton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":4,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":35,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":60,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":73,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen was born about 1255, in Cheshire, England. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Richard Fouleshurst. She died about 1331, in her hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"about 1255–about 1331":"umbes 1255–umbes 1331","1252–1299":"1252–1299","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1277–1338":"1277–1338","1278–1340":"1278–1340","1255–1331":"1255–1331","1340":"1340","1252":"1252","1290":"1290","1338":"1338","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1277":"1277","1299":"1299","1276":"1276","ABT 1278":"umbes 1278","1331":"1331","about 1255":"umbes 1255","about 1277":"umbes 1277","about 1299":"umbes 1299","about 1331":"umbes 1331","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Crewe, Cheshire, England":"Crewe, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Edleston, Cheshire, England":"Edleston, Cheshire, England","Egerton, Cheshire, England":"Egerton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1255–about 1331":"noin 1255–noin 1331","1252–1299":"1252–1299","1276–Male":"1276–Kuollut","1277–1338":"1277–1338","1278–1340":"1278–1340","1255–1331":"1255–1331","1340":"1340","1252":"1252","1290":"1290","1338":"1338","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1277":"1277","1299":"1299","1276":"1276","ABT 1278":"noin 1278","1331":"1331","about 1255":"noin 1255","about 1277":"noin 1277","about 1299":"noin 1299","about 1331":"noin 1331","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Crewe, Cheshire, England":"Crewe